## 🔄 CI/CD Pipeline Flow

```
Code Push → Jenkins Trigger → Build Docker Image → Push to Registry → Deploy to Kubernetes
```

**Jenkinsfile stages:**
1. **Checkout** — Pull source code from GitHub
2. **Build** — Build Docker image
3. **Test** — Run application tests
4. **Push** — Push image to Docker registry
5. **Deploy** — Apply Kubernetes manifests

---

## 🐳 Run with Docker

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/mohitkamboj0228-ops/devops-project.git
cd devops-project

# Build the Docker image
docker build -t devops-app .

# Run the container
docker run -p 5000:5000 devops-app
```

---

## ☸️ Deploy to Kubernetes

```bash
# Apply deployment
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml

# Apply service
kubectl apply -f service.yml

# Check status
kubectl get pods
kubectl get services
```

---

## 📋 Prerequisites

- Docker 20.x+
